menu_status_animals
[TITLE]The Manual:  Animals[/TITLE]
[C:7:0:1]How to Get Here[C:7:0:0]
[B]
Press [IKEY:D_STATUS] from the main view, scroll to "Animals" and press [IKEY:SELECT].
[B][B]
[C:7:0:1]Description[C:7:0:0]
[B]
This lists all of the animals in your fortress.
Use [IKEY:STANDARDSCROLL_UP][IKEY:STANDARDSCROLL_DOWN][IKEY:STANDARDSCROLL_PAGEUP][IKEY:STANDARDSCROLL_PAGEDOWN] to scroll.
[B]
You can make tame animals available as pets here.  Some dwarves like to keep a certain type of animal as a pet.  You can view pet preferences in the unit profile.
[B]
[LINK:data/help/unit_profile]Unit Profiles[/LINK]
[B]
If an animal is not somebody's pet, you can also designate it to be slaughtered.  The slaughter occurs at the butcher's shop.
